Abuja (Sundiata Post) – Peoples Democratic Party candidate in Ekiti State governorship election, Bisi Kolawole, on Saturday, voted at his Ward 08, Unit 01. He commended the Independent National Electoral Commission over the Bimodal Voter Accreditation System. The PDP candidate, however, warned against “manipulation”. Kolawole, who said the use of BVAS had accelerated, the process of voting, said, “There is an improvement generally in the workings of INEC”, adding that, “The process, compared to previous elections is a great improvement. He said, “The accreditation and voting are done simultaneously. The process has been accelerated by this. There is an improvement by INEC. “We just hope there won’t be manipulation. The process is ongoing. “I cannot say there won’t be manipulation of the process, but the security is doing fine. As of now, we are having a peaceful process.” (Punch) .....Commission says new method’ll complement manual process Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The ruling All Progressives Congress, Peoples Democratic Party, Social Democratic Party and 13 other political parties are jostling to produce the next governor of Ekiti State in today’s election. The exercise is scheduled to hold across the 2,445 polling… In "Top Stories" ....Assures of transparency, security and peaceful conduct of polls By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - Ahead of the governorship election scheduled to hold on Saturday in Ekiti State, the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC), said it has deployed four National Commissioners, eight Resident Electoral Commissioners and many senior officials… In "Top Stories" By STEPHEN ADELEYE LOKOJA- Hajia Ramatu Attah, a senatorial aspirant for Kogi Central on the platform of APC, has rejected the outcome of last week’s senatorial primary election in the zone. Attah insisted that, ”there was no APC primaries in the zone, and no candidate emerged”. The Spokesperson for the… In "Politics"